High‑Level Architecture
Data collection (not in scope) : Raw sensor and touch events are captured during user sessions.

Feature extraction : SessionLevelFeatureExtractor processes each session to produce a CSV row of ~441 numeric features. This code is run offline to generate _training_sessions.csv and _testing_sessions.csv for each user.

Data cleansing : Phase 1 script removes constant, missing, and highly correlated features, producing cleaned_features.csv.

Feature ranking (Phases 2A‑2C) : Three independent ranking methods are applied to the 13 (or all) development users, producing three ranked lists.

Consensus ranking : Phase 3 merges the rankings using a weighted percentile average.

K‑selection / hyperparameter tuning : Phase 5 / LOUO tuning script evaluates candidate feature sets (or iterates over K) with OCSVM, selecting the best hyperparameters (nu, gamma, threshold) that maximise TAR while respecting FAR and FRR constraints.

Final model : For each user, an OCSVM is trained on their genuine sessions using the chosen feature subset and the optimal hyperparameters.

Deployment : The trained model and scaler are saved and can be loaded to score new sessions in real time.

